{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_t6rfzq9asgry_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: N/A\nURL: https://hermetic.com/_media/93beast.fea.st/files/section1/777/liber_777_revised.pdf\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Aleister Crowley\nHighlights:\nSVMMÆ\n[...]\nUlthar - Sarkomand - Inquanok ñ Leeds \n2004 \nLIBER DCCLXXVII. A COMPLETE DICTIONARY OF THE \nCORRESPONDENCES OF ALL MAGICAL ELEMENTS, re\u0002printed with extensive additions, making it the only \nstandard comprehensive book of reference ever published. \nIt is to the language of Occultism what Webster or Murray \nis to the English language. \nìPrÊmonstrance of A∴A∴,î Equinox III (1). \nCONTENTS \n* EDITORIAL PREFACE (to 777 Revised) . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . vi \n INTRODUCTION (from the first edition) . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . xi \n THE TREE OF LIFE . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . xviii \n TABLES OF CORRESPONDENCE\n[...]\n. . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n[...]\nEDITORIAL PREFACE* \n777 is a qabalistic dictionary of ceremonial magic, oriental \nmysticism, comparative religion, and symbology. It is also a \nhandbook for ceremonial invocation and for checking the validity \nof dreams and visions. It is indispendisble to those who wish to \ncorrelate these apparently diverse studies. It was published \nprivately by Aleister Crowley in 1909, has long been out of print \nand is now practically unprocurable. \nCrowley, who had a phenomenal memory, wrote it at \nBournemouth in a week without reference booksóor so he \nclaimed in an unpublished section of his ìConfessions.îÜ It is \nnot, however, entirely original. Ninety per cent of the Hebrew, \nthe four colour scales, and the order and attribution of the Tarot \ntrumps are as taught in the Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn \nwith its inner circle of the Rose of Ruby and the Cross of Gold \n(R.R. et A.C.) \nThis Order is still in existence, though it has changed its name \nand is dormant, for it no longer accepts probationers.á It was the\n[...]\n, consists of an essay on\n[...]\nTHE TREE OF LIFE \nCOL. XII. This arrangement is the basis of the \nwhole system of this book. Besides the 10\nnumbers and the 22 letters, it is divisible into 3\ncolumns, 4 planes, 7 planes, 7 palaces, etc. etc. \nTABLE OF \nCORRESPONDENCES\n[...]\n2 TABLE I \nI. \nKey \nScale. \nII.* \nHebrew Names \nof Numbers \nand Letters.\nIII.\nEnglish of Col. II. \nIV.* \nConsciousness \nof the Adept. \nV.* \nGod-Names in Assiah. \n \n0 { }wa\n[ws }ya\nr\n[...]\nof Assiah.\n[...]\nVII.\n[...]\nEnglish of Col. VI.\n[...]\nof Qliphoth\n[...]\n. . . . .\n[...]\nThe Paths of the Sepher Yetzirah. \nXIV. \nGeneral Attribution of Tarot. \nXV.*\n[...]\nThe King Scale of Colour \n(y). \n \n0\n[...]\n. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n[...]\n31 bis [Liber] [[Bacchus]] The Holy Ghost \n[Insufficient information.]\n[...]\nI (continued) 1\n\n---\n\nTitle: Thelemagick Library - Liber DCCLXXVII - Book 777\nURL: https://www.tarrdaniel.com/documents/Thelemagick/publication/english/Liber_DCCLXXVII.html\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n| 14. | XIV. | The General Attribution of Tarot | 97. | XCVII. | Parts of the Soul |\n[...]\n| 22. | XXII. | Small selection of Hindu Deities | 105. | CV. | English of Col. CIV. |\n[...]\n| 71. | LXXI. | The Court Cards of the\n[...]\n, with the Spheres of their Celestial Dominatino — Wands | 153. | CLIII. | Perfumes (Succedent) |\n[...]\n| 175. | CLXXV. | Hebrew Letters |\n| 176. | CLXXVI. | Numerical Value of Col. CLXXV. |\n| 177. | CLXXVII. | Yetziratic Attribution of Col. CLXXV. |\n| 178. | CLXXVIII. | Geomantic Intelligences |\n| 179. | CLXXIX. | Numbers printed on Tarot Trumps |\n| 180. | CLXXX. | Title of Tarot Trumps |\n| 181. | CLXXXI. | Correct Design of Tarot Trumps |\n| 182. | CLXXXII. | The Human Body |\n| 183. | CLXXXIII. | Legendary Orders of Being |\n[...]\nCLXXV. Hebrew Letters, CL